p.em: "With a sufficient number of users of an API, it does not matter what you promise in the contract: all observable behaviors of your system will be depended on by somebody."

div.p: Translation: The upstream chart maintainer can't see YOUR live state. Their "safe" change can clobber YOUR critical values.

pre.code: # What's actually running maxConnections: 500 # Someone changed this!

div.p: 1. Default Clobbering K8s set a default you didn't know about. Your template overwrites it.
2. Hardcoded Clobbering Value works for dev, breaks prod. Change affects ALL environments.
3. Upstream Clobbering Chart maintainer changes a default. Your production breaks on upgrade.
4. Break-Glass Clobbering Someone fixed prod manually. GitOps reconciles it back.

pre.code:
$ cub-scout map orphans ConfigMap/postgres-config (Native) Live state differs from Git - may be clobbered on next sync
$ cub-scout trace deploy/postgres -n prod HelmRelease/postgresql Values: maxConnections=200
Live: maxConnections=500 Someone changed this directly! Next reconciliation will reset to 200.
